    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesis is that a carbohydrate-free diet, ingested for 3 days, results
      in a change in blood glucose that is similar to the change observed after 3 days of fasting.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      In addition to plasma glucose concentrations, other hormones and metabolites known to be
      affected by fasting will be measured. These include insulin and glucagon, which are hormones
      that have an important role in regulating fuel use in the body.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
